{"lemma":"فَلْقُ","slug":"فَلْقُ","root":"ف.ل.ق","root_slug":"ف-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَلْقُ","root":"فلق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n34536","n34537","n34538"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, to cleave"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, to cleave; to cause to break (dawn)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to split, to cleave"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَلَقَ (falaqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"split, cleft, fissure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fissure, cleft, kloof"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"daybreak, dawn","examples":[{"text":"قُلْ أَعُوذُ بِرَبِّ الْفَلَقِ","english":"Say: I seek refuge with the Lord of the daybreak"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of فِلْقَة (filqa)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34536","headword_ar":"فَلْقٌ","root":"flq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (AHeyth, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqN","text_ar":"فَلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) the former said by AHeyth to be the more correct, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A split, fissure, cleft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"longitudinal division;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~N","text_ar":"شَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuluwqN","text_ar":"فُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqN","text_ar":"فَلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K, TA) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqN","text_ar":"فَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"?] signifies also [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fissure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~N","text_ar":"شَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a mountain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliqN","text_ar":"فَالِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEob","text_ar":"شِعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ravine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mararotu biHar~apK fiyhaA fuluwqN","text_ar":"مَرَرْتُ بِحَرَّةٍ فِيهَا فُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwqF","text_ar":"شُقُوقً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I passed by a stony tract such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~ap","text_ar":"حَرَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which were fissures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clefts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY rijolihi fuluwqN","text_ar":"فِى رِجْلِهِ فُلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uquwqN","text_ar":"شُقُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his foot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leg, are fissures"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clefts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (As, S, O, * K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~amaniY mino faloqi fiyhi","text_ar":"كَلَّمَنِى مِنْ فَلْقِ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqi","text_ar":"فِلْقِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, S, K,) the former of which is the more known, (TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino $aq~ihi","text_ar":"مِنْ شَقِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spoke to me from out the fissure of his mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his lips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not by means of a spokesman]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drabahu EalaY faloqi raA^osihi","text_ar":"ضرَبَهُ عَلَى فَلْقِ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck him on the place where his hair was separated, the middle of his head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqN","text_ar":"فَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  And see the paragraph here following, last quarter."}],"source_refs":["AHeyth","TA","S","O","Lh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n34537","headword_ar":"فِلْقٌ","root":"flq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph.       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqapN","text_ar":"فِلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rod,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"branch, that is split in two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) [i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in halves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of which are then made two bows, each whereof is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqN","text_ar":"فِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each half"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~u $iq~K","text_ar":"كُلُّ شِقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~K","text_ar":"شَقٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what is thus split is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqN","text_ar":"فِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and thus is termed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bow that is made of the half of a branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the branch being split in two;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is also termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN filoqN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ فِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter word being thus used as an epithet, on the authority of Lh: or, as AHn says, the bow termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqN","text_ar":"فِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the wood whereof it has been made has been previously split in two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"three, pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and he also says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliyqN","text_ar":"فَلِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN faliyqN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ فَلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bow of which the piece of wood has been split in two pieces."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyjN","text_ar":"شَرِيجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wonderful thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliyqN","text_ar":"فَلِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayolaqN","text_ar":"فَيْلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliyqapN","text_ar":"فَلِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, * TA,) of which last an ex. occurs in the prov.,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA EajabiY lih`*ahi AlfaliyqahN\n                      \n                     \n                        halo tagoliban~a AlquwabaA='u Alr~iyqahu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O my wonder at this wonderful thing! Does the ringworm indeed overcome the spittle?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: AA says, the meaning is, that he was in wonder at the alteration of usual occurrences; for the spittle usually dispels the ringworm, so he spat upon his ringworm, but it did not become healed:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqwbA='","text_ar":"القوبا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is made an agent; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alryqp","text_ar":"الريقة"},{"kind":"text","text":", an objective complement. (O, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqapN","text_ar":"فِلْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA, accord. to the CK ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqN","text_ar":"فَلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliyqN","text_ar":"فَلِيقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faliyqapN","text_ar":"فَلِيقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqaY","text_ar":"فَلْقَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqaY","text_ar":"فَلَقَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayolaqN","text_ar":"فَيْلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O and CK,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafolaqapN","text_ar":"مَفْلَقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrd, O, K.) The Arabs say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA lilofaliyqapi","text_ar":"يَا لِلْفَلِيقَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O"},{"kind":"text","text":"[come with succour]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the calamity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a biEulaqa fulaqa","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ بِعُلَقَ فُلَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) imperfectly decl., (S, O,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought to pass"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which was"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2442},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a calamity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEulaqF fulaqK","text_ar":"بِعُلَقً فُلَقٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) or this means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a very wonderful thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n34538","headword_ar":"فَلَقٌ","root":"flq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqN","text_ar":"فَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence, in two places. ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"daybreak,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faloqN","text_ar":"فَلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Z and others; (TA;) and thus the former has been expl. as signifying in the Kur cxiii. 1: (S, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what has broken"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anflq","text_ar":"انفلق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwd","text_ar":"عَمُود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dawn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr. K, TA;) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bright gleam of dawn; of the dawn that rises and spreads, filling the horizon with its whiteness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending light that is like the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long tent called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamuwd","text_ar":"عَمُود"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or [simply] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of daybreak"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K: *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing of the daybreak"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqu AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"فَلَقُ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bright shining, of the daybreak"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dawn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwaA^aboyanu mino falaqi AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"هُوَاَبْيَنُ مِنْ فَلَقِ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraqi AlS~uboHi","text_ar":"فَرَقِ الصُّبْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is more distinct than what has broken of the bright gleam of dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b3-  And [hence,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plain appearing of the truth after its having been dubious."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A law,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed, place of the earth, between two kills,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated grounds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliqN","text_ar":"فَالِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliqapN","text_ar":"فَالِقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last is said by Aboo-Kheyreh, or some other, of the Arabs of the desert, to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the midst of mountains, giving growth to trees, a place where people alight and where camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other cattle, remain during the cold night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"saying that the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliq","text_ar":"فَالِق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard and level, ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqN","text_ar":"فَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuloqaAnN","text_ar":"فُلْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afolaAqN","text_ar":"اَفْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqN","text_ar":"فَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAliqN","text_ar":"فَالِقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wide tract of land"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, between two extended tracts of sand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) and the pl. of the latter word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuloqaAnN","text_ar":"فُلْقَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HujoraAnN","text_ar":"حُجْرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjirN","text_ar":"حَاجِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfalaqu","text_ar":"الفَلَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hell;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahan~amu","text_ar":"جَهَنَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain well"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~N","text_ar":"جُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es-Suddee, O, K.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The whole creation; all the beings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, that are created."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, S, O, K.) This, accord. to some, is the meaning in the Kur cxiii. 1. (S, O.)       -A5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What remains, of milk, in the bottom of the bowl;"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence one says, (in reviling a person, attributing to him meanness, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A@bona $aAribi Alfalaqi","text_ar":"يَا ا@بْنَ شَارِبِ الفَلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O son of the drinker of what remains"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And The milk"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is in a dissundered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curdled, state, by reason of sourness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutafal~iqN","text_ar":"مُتَفَلِّقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoTarap","text_ar":"مِقْطَرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the keeper of a prison;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, * K;) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of stocks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood in which are holes of the size of the shank, wherein men are confined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thieves and waylayers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a row:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) whence the saying of Z,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAta fulaAnN fiY Al$~afaqi waAlfalaqi mina Al$~afaqi A_ilaY Alfalaqi","text_ar":"بَاتَ فُلَانٌ فِى الشَّفَقِ وَالفَلَقِ مِنَ الشَّفَقِ اـِلَى الفَلَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one passed the night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in fear and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mqTrp","text_ar":"مقطرة"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"the time of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the redness of the region of sunset after the setting of the sun until the dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falaqapN","text_ar":"فَلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","TA","Zj","K"]}]}}